CatDescriptText: Mr. Abram Wooten, 1241 N. Franklin Street was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 19, 1958, pg. 9, with question: "Do you think that a business recession has hit the United States? If so, how has it affected you?"  Answer reads: "Yes, because supply has caught up with demand.  However, it hasn't affected me.  I'm a worker at Isaly's Dairy store."
TitMainTitle: Abram Wooten standing in front of brick wall with painted sign advertising meat products
